---
intent: >
  Verify the `@latest` dist-tag amendment is fully applied across the
  install config source, the InstallFooter component, and the test suite,
  and update the test description to clarify that `@latest` is the
  required dist-tag (not merely "no version pinning").
---

## Plan

1. [x] **Verify `@latest` in `buildInstallConfig/index.ts`**

   Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions.md`

   The `.aide` spec now requires `@aidemd-mcp/server@latest` in both the
   `mcpConfig.args` array and the `commandSequence` step-1 JSON block.
   Open `src/service/install/buildInstallConfig/index.ts` and confirm both
   occurrences use `@aidemd-mcp/server@latest`. If either still uses the
   bare package name (`@aidemd-mcp/server` without `@latest`), update it.

   Files: `src/service/install/buildInstallConfig/index.ts`

   Acceptance: both `args` arrays in the file contain exactly
   `"@aidemd-mcp/server@latest"`.

2. [x] **Verify `@latest` in `InstallFooter/index.tsx`**

   Read: `coding-playbook/client/components.md`

   The inline `<code>` element in the InstallFooter must show
   `npx @aidemd-mcp/server@latest init`. Open
   `src/components/shared/InstallFooter/index.tsx` and confirm the code
   element text matches. If it still uses the bare package name, update it.

   Files: `src/components/shared/InstallFooter/index.tsx`

   Acceptance: the rendered text is exactly
   `npx @aidemd-mcp/server@latest init`.

3. [x] **Update the test description and add a positive `@latest` assertion**

   Read: `coding-playbook/workflow/testing.md`

   Open `src/service/install/buildInstallConfig/index.test.ts`. Two changes:

   3a. Rename the existing test from
   `"no version pinning in args (no version numbers in args array)"` to
   `"rejects semver pins but allows @latest dist-tag"`. The test body
   (the regex check against `/@[\^~]?\d+\.\d+/`) is still correct and
   should stay as-is â€” it guards against semver pins and does not
   false-positive on `@latest`.

   3b. Add a new test case:
   `"args contain @latest dist-tag"`. This test should assert that
   every element in `mcpConfig.mcpServers.aide.args` that starts with
   `@aidemd-mcp/server` includes the `@latest` suffix. Use a simple
   string check (e.g., `expect(arg).toContain("@latest")`). This is
   the positive counterpart to the existing negative regex test â€” it
   confirms the dist-tag is present, not just that semver is absent.

   Files: `src/service/install/buildInstallConfig/index.test.ts`

   Acceptance: `rtk vitest run` passes with all five tests green
   (the original four plus the new one).

## Decisions

- **Rename, don't delete the existing test.** The semver-pin regex guard
  is still valuable â€” it catches regressions like `@0.3.0` or `@^1.2.3`.
  Renaming it clarifies its purpose without losing coverage.

- **Separate positive and negative assertions.** The existing test proves
  "no semver pins." The new test proves "`@latest` is present." These are
  independent properties. A future change could accidentally strip the
  dist-tag entirely (bare package name) and the semver test would still
  pass â€” the positive assertion catches that gap.

- **Steps 1 and 2 are verification, not implementation.** The code
  changes were already applied. The plan includes them so QA has explicit
  checkpoints to confirm correctness rather than assuming prior work was
  complete.

- **No changes to the InstallConfig type.** The type
  (`src/types/install.ts`) defines `args` as `string[]`, which already
  accommodates the `@latest` suffix. No type-level change needed.
